# Update conversation transcript

The project keeps a full transcript of AI conversations in **AI_CONVERSATION_TRANSCRIPT.md** at the project root.

## Rule

**After completing any substantive exchange** (code changes, multi-step tasks, or meaningful Q&A), update the transcript:

1. Open `AI_CONVERSATION_TRANSCRIPT.md`.
2. Append a new section in the same format as existing ones:
   - `## Conversation N` (use the next number after the last `## Conversation` in the file).
   - `### User` — Short summary of what the user asked or requested (can be one or two sentences).
   - `### Assistant (response)` — Concise summary of what was implemented or answered: list changes (files, behavior), and any important clarifications or decisions.
3. Keep the existing trailing line: `*Transcript will be updated as the conversation continues.*`

## When to update

- After finishing a task or set of edits (e.g. feature, refactor, bugfix).
- After answering questions that affect understanding of the codebase or decisions.
- You may batch several small back-and-forth turns into one “Conversation N” if they form a single topic.

Do not add a new section for every single message; group by topic or task. When in doubt, add an update at the end of your response so the transcript stays current.
